TopicTitle: Show off your awesome KSP pictures!

Articles.Content:
"I feel the spring breeze, but I know its one of my dreams; my life is torn apart at the seams."

"They tell me not to give up, but do I even have a choice? They are the ones who took away my voice..."

"I need a hero, someone who will save me.

But they don't get it, telling me to fight bravely."

"I have been fighting and already 'round the bend

Sitting down and waiting for this nightmare to end."

.......
My recreation of the famous 'pale blue dot' picture by NASA, on my first landing on the mun (about 4 months ago).
it's been a while since i made this but i havent shared it so..

A few pics from the Eve Rocks challenge (level 5) entry, that worked as planned, but ended up as a failure due to me assuming that science data can be transferred between any docked vehicles.

I have a few from some recent missions I did after installing some visual mods.

Finally spending time playing KSP instead of modding it.  MOL-MIR station, with the MOL-OCO science/power module on the zenith port, the MOL-Expansion module on the forward port, and the MOL-Pirs docking adapter on the expansion nadir port (with a visiting Apollo D2).

Oh, and the Belle Orbital Tug still attached on the MOL-Expansion forward port.

A few pics from the Little Flyer's trip to a land of lakes and mountains.
I thought I'd give props another chance today.

It's been a while since I have posted anything on the forum, but here you go   8 launches including a working spaceshuttle.
